The project budget can be exceeded as users enter documents. If the system is configured to control the budget on document entry, it check whether an entered document is within the cost budget of the project, taking into consideration the portion of the budget that has already been consumed. That helps you to control the documents you are creating and can be useful for a person who approves these documents. When you enter or process one of the following documents related to a project, and the amount of a document line exceeds the cost budget of the corresponding project budget line (even if the project budget has no corresponding budget line), you will see a warning:[anchor|#_77315587-7956-4d65-8d43-e34405727c58] *A purchase order of the ''Open'' or ''Drop Ship'' type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form. *:For a document of the ''On Hold'' or ''Pending Approval'' status, you can see a warning in the '''Ext. Cost''' column on the '''Document Details''' tab for the lines that exceed the project budget. The warning is also shown in the Summary area. *An AP bill on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form. *:For a document of the ''On Hold'', ''Pending Approval'', or ''Balanced'', you can see a warning in the '''Ext. Cost''' column on the '''Document Details''' tab for the lines that exceed the project budget. The warning is also shown in the Summary area. *A change order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_80_00|Change Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PM308000|PM308000]) form. *:For a document of the ''On Hold'' or ''Pending Approval'' status, you can see a warning in the '''Amount''' column on the '''Commitment''' tab for the lines that exceed the project budget. The warning is also shown in the Summary area.
The warning message in a document line shows you how much the line amount exceeds the budget. The system compares the document line with the corresponding cost budget line of the project and show you the following amounts in the warning:[anchor|#_ea172f54-6c0c-4eee-81e0-9a187f19b1e3] *''Available'': The amount of the budget that you can process with the document *:The available amount is calculated as the difference between the ''Budgeted'' and ''Consumed'' amounts. The budgeted amount is the revised budgeted amount of the budget line. The consumed amount is the amount that has been already spent—that is, the sum of the actual amount and the committed open amount of the budget line. *''Remaining'': The amount that exceeds the budget *:The remaining amount is calculated as the difference between the ''Available'' and ''Document'' amounts. The document amount is the total amount (the '''Ext. Cost''' minus the '''Discount Amount''') of all the lines of the validated document that correspond to the same budget line. including the current one.
For example, you have budgeted the cost of $400 for the project (the budgeted amount). You have already spent $150 (the consumed amount). When you create for the project an AP bill for the amount of $300 (the document amount), the system will show you the following warning:{br}
''Budgeted: 400.00, Consumed: 150.00, Available: 250.00, Document: 300.00, Remaining: -50.00''{br}{TOC}

After the project budget has been agreed upon, you can lock the original figures from further editing. After the original values are locked, you can still update the revised budget figures. This gives you the ability to control how accurately the budget was estimated.{br}
When you decide to prevent any changes to original budgeted values of the project, you click the '''Lock Budget''' action on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form. When the action is applied for the project, on the '''Revenue Budget''' and '''Cost Budget''' tabs, the following columns become read-only:[anchor|#_c12321f4-1985-45a7-b1b7-ceb443c17adb] *'''Original Budgeted Quantity''' * '''Unit Rate''' * '''Original Budgeted Amount'''.
You can still edit the budgeted values in the '''Revised Budgeted Quantity''' and '''Revised Budgeted Amount''' columns.{br}
Once you decide that making changes to original budgeted values are allowed for the project, you unlock the project budget by clicking '''Unlock Budget''' action on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] form.

In this activity, you will learn how to prevent the original budget values of the project from being edited.[anchor|#_104290cd-7e83-4d23-ba52-75ebfef140d0]((({S:Danger}The following activity is based on the ''U100'' dataset. If you are using another dataset, or if any system settings have been changed in ''U100'', these changes can affect the workflow of the activity and the results of the processing. To avoid any issues, restore the ''U100'' dataset to its initial state. ))){br}{TOC} ==Story== Suppose that the HM&rsquo;s Bakery and Cafe customer has ordered a juicer, along with the services of installation and training for its employees on operating the juicer from the SweetLife Fruits & Jams company. SweetLife&rsquo;s project accountant has created a project. Before the work on the project has begun, the customer has requested 12 hours of training instead of initially ordered eight hours.{br}
Acting as the project accountant, you will change the original budgeted values of the project before proceeding to the execution stage and lock the budget to prevent the original budgeted values from further editing.The training will take 16 hours instead of 12 and you will adjust revised budgeted values to bill the customer for all the provided services. ==Configuration Overview== For the purposes of this activity, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, the ''Project Accounting'' feature has been enabled to support the project accounting functionality.{br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form, the ''HMBAKERY11'' project has been created and the ''PHASE1'' and ''PHASE2'' project tasks have been created for the project. On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form, the ''INSTALL'' and ''TRAINING'' non-stock items have been configured.{br}
