==Step: Locking the Project Budget== To update the project budget and protect the original budgeted values from being edited, do the following.[anchor|#_a7fc6e3b-d40e-45c3-8b1a-031a0a172a9b] #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form, open the ''HMBAKERY11'' project, and on the '''Revenue Budget''' tab, review the revenue budget of the project. #In the revenue budget line with the ''PHASE2'' task and ''TRAINING'' inventory item, enter <tt>12.00</tt> as the '''Original Budgeted Quantity'''. #Save your changes to the project. #On the form toolbar, click '''Actions''' > '''Lock Budget''' to prevent the original budgeted values from being edited. #:Notice that you cannot adjust original budget values in the '''Original Budgeted Quantity''', '''Unit Rate''', and '''Original Budgeted Amount''' columns but you still can edit the '''Revised Budgeted Quantity''' and '''Revised Budgeted Amount'''. #In the revenue budget line with the ''PHASE2'' task and ''TRAINING'' inventory item, enter <tt>16.00</tt> as the '''Revised Budgeted Quantity'''. #Save your changes to the project.

When you select an inventory item in a project budget line, the system automatically populates the unit rate of the line. The mechanism of retrieving the unit rate depends on the budget line type and is supported on the following forms: [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_20_80_00|Project Templates] ([~/?ScreenId=PM208000|PM208000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_80_00|Change Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PM308000|PM308000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_85_00|Change Requests] ([~/?ScreenId=PM308500|PM308500]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_45_00|Project Quotes] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304500|PM304500]), and [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_90_00|Project Budget] ([~/?ScreenId=PM309000|PM309000]). ==Retrieving the Unit Rate for a Revenue Budget Line== When you select an inventory item in a revenue budget line—that is, a line with the account group of the income type, the system automatically fills in the unit rate of the line with the item price. The system searches for an applicable price of the inventory item that is effective on the start date of the project or the document date among the sales prices existing in the system. For more details on how the system searches the price, see [HelpRoot_PricesAndDiscounts\PriceDiscount_Sales_Price_Selection_GeneralInfo|Automatic Price Selection: Rules of Price Selection]. ==Retrieving the Unit Rate for a Cost Budget Line== When you select an inventory item in a cost budget line—that is, a line with the account group of the expense type, the system automatically fills in the unit rate of the line with the item cost.{br}
If the type of the selected inventory item of the budget line is labor—that is, the ''Labor'' option is selected for the item in the '''Type''' box in the '''Item Defaults''' section on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_20_99_00|Labor Cost Rates] ([~/?ScreenId=PM209900|PM209900]) form, the system retrieves the labor cost rate of the ''Labor Item'' type that is associated with the same inventory item and that has an effective date that satisfies the start date of project or the document date.{br}
If no labor cost rate is found or the type of the selected inventory item of the budget line is not ''Labor'', the system retrieves the following costs depending on the type of the inventory item:[anchor|#ul_plz_xvn_x2b] *For a stock item: The '''Average Cost''' of the item from the '''Price/Cost Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_25_00|Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202500|IN202500]) form *For a non-stock item: The '''Current Cost''' of the item from the '''Price/Cost Information''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form
The following diagram illustrates the logic the system uses to select the cost for an inventory item.[anchor|#_3a903e16-5b56-4d12-ae1d-be7c6d910794][anchor|#_f471f8e3-fc92-4c91-b110-552f948033ec][image:UserGuide/Images/diag_Projects_Unit_Rate.png|popup|450px]

Acumatica ERP supports project quotes, which you can enter and modify on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_45_00|Project Quotes] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304500|PM304500]) form. A project quote is used to estimate a potential project and to send a proposal to the customer; you use the quote before you create a project in the system and begin billing and accounting for revenues and costs. Each modification of a project quote can be printed and sent to the customer for review, and you can modify the quote as many times as is necessary until an agreement is reached. After the customer agrees to the terms of the quote, you can convert the winning quote to a project. ==Learning Objectives== You will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#ul_nwj_gch_tbb] *Create a project quote *Specify the settings of the quote by using a project template *Specify the estimation lines of the project quote *Create a project based on the project quote *Review the interaction between project quotes and opportunities
==Applicable Scenarios== If you want to send a proposal to the customer before you create a project, or if you need to agree with the customer about the terms of a potential project before creating the project, you can use the functionality of project quotes.[anchor|#section_fdf_x42_p2b] ==Creation of Project Quotes== You create a project quote on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_45_00|Project Quotes] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304500|PM304500]) form.{br}
For a new project quote, you specify the following settings:[anchor|#ul_fsf_yfs_p2b] *The description of the project quote. *The project template, which the system uses to populate the project tasks, attributes, and project manager of the project quote. You can change these default settings, if needed. *:If you first specify the tasks, attributes, and project manager of the project quote, and then select the project template, you can either replace your specified settings with the settings of the project template or leave your specified settings. *The business account associated with the project quote. *:Based on the settings specified for the selected business account, on the '''Billing Information''' tab, the system inserts the contact information and the financial details. You can override these settings, if needed. *Optional: The project tasks on the '''Project Tasks''' tab. *The estimated labor and material costs and prices on the '''Estimation''' tab. If you convert the project quote to a project, the system populates the revenue and cost budget of the project based on the settings specified on this tab.
When you click '''Save''' on the form toolbar, the system creates a project quote with the ''Draft'' status. When you have specified all the needed settings and have finished modify the project quote, you submit the quote by clicking '''Submit Quote''' on the form toolbar. A submitted project quote is assigned the ''Prepared'' status and you cannot modify it until it is assigned the ''Draft'' status back.{br}
You can email a submitted project quote to the customer by invoking the '''Send Quote''' action on the form toolbar. Once the project quote is sent, the system performs the following actions:[anchor|#ul_l3h_xkk_nlb] *Creates and lists the corresponding email activity on the '''Activities''' tab of the form *Attaches the quote to the email activity (in the form of a report) and sends it to the recipient *Changes the status of the quote to ''Sent'' {br}
If you need to modify a project quote, you click '''Edit Quote''' on the form toolbar. The quote is assigned the ''Draft'' status and can be modified.((({S:Warn}If you need to modify an existing project quote but also want to leave its original version intact (for example, for historical purposes), you can create a copy of the project quote by invoking the '''Copy Quote''' action; you then modify the copy. ))) ==Estimation Lines of a Project Quotes== The lines on the '''Estimation''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_45_00|Project Quotes] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304500|PM304500]) form represent the estimated revenue and costs of a project quote, which the system converts to lines of the revenue and cost budgets when you create a project based on the project quote.{br}
An estimation line with an account group specified in the '''Revenue Account Group''' column establishes revenue; the '''Ext. Price''' of the line is the estimated revenue amount. An estimation line with an account group specified in the '''Cost Account Group''' column establishes costs; the '''Ext. Cost''' of the line is the estimated cost amount. Estimation lines with both the '''Revenue Account Group''' and the '''Cost Account Group''' specified establish revenue and costs at the same time.[anchor|#section_kcj_x42_p2b] ==Creation of a Project Based on a Project Quote== You can convert a project quote to a project if the project quote has the ''Prepared'' or ''Sent'' status—that is, if the project quote has been submitted or emailed. Before you convert the project quote, the following settings must be specified for it in the Summary area of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_45_00|Project Quotes] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304500|PM304500]) form:[anchor|#ul_ejx_dpv_q2b] *'''Project Template''': The template to be used for the creation of the project *'''Business Account''': The customer of the project *'''New Project ID''': The identifier of the project
For a project quote that satisfies the basic requirements listed above, on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_45_00|Project Quotes] form, you click '''Convert to Project''' to convert the project quote to a project. In the '''Convert to Project''' dialog box, which opens, you define the settings to be used for the created project and click '''OK'''.{br}
Once a project is created based on a project quote, the quote is assigned the ''Closed'' status. If you delete the project, the system assigns the ''Prepared'' status to the project quote. You can assign the ''Draft'' status to the project quote and edit it, if needed, and create a project based on the project quote again.{br}
In a project created based on a project quote, a link to the project quote is displayed in the '''Quote Ref. Nbr.''' box on the '''Summary''' tab ('''Quote''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form.[anchor|#section_i3l_d4p_mcb] ==Workflow of Project Quotes== The following diagram illustrates the workflow of processing a project quote.[anchor|#fig_fhq_2nv_q2b][anchor|#image_ghq_2nv_q2b][image:UserGuide/Images/diag_Project_Quotes_Workflow.png|popup|350px]

This topic describes how opportunities are integrated with project quotes.[anchor|#section_fdf_x42_p2b]
==Creation of Project Quotes Based on an Opportunity==
While you are viewing an opportunity on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR304000|CR304000]) form, you can begin the process of creating a quote based on the opportunity by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Create Quote''' on the form toolbar. The system opens the '''Create New Quote''' dialog box, where you specify basic settings and initiate the creation of the quote.{br}

The system creates the project quote based on the opportunity and opens the project quote on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_45_00|Project Quotes] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304500|PM304500]) form. In the Summary area, the system inserts the identifier of the opportunity in the '''Opportunity ID''' box and copies the following settings from the opportunity:[anchor|#ul_fsf_yfs_p2b]
*The business account
*The description (in the '''Subject''' box)
*The owner

Once you save the project quote associated with the opportunity, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] form, the project quote is listed on the '''Quotes''' tab along with the other project and sales quotes linked to the opportunity.
==The Primary Project Quote of an Opportunity==
The first quote created for an opportunity is always the primary quote. That is, on the '''Quotes''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR304000|CR304000]) form, the primary quote has the check box in the '''Primary''' column selected. On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_45_00|Project Quotes] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304500|PM304500]) form, the '''Primary''' check box is selected for this quote in the Summary area.{br}

The primary project quote of an opportunity reflects the opportunity value in sales reports. However, the details of the project quote and the actions applicable to the quote are not reflected in the opportunity.{br}

Starting from the second quote, you can create either a primary quote or a non-primary quote for an opportunity. Also, you can make an existing quote the primary quote for the opportunity. (This causes the previous primary quote to become non-primary, because each opportunity can have only one primary quote.)
==Creation of a Project Based on a Project Quote==
If a project quote has been created based on an opportunity, you can create a project based on the project quote only if the project quote is the primary quote of the opportunity.{br}

If the project has been created based on the primary project quote of an opportunity, on the '''Quotes''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR304000|CR304000]) form, the identifier of the created project is shown in the '''Project ID''' column of the project quote.{br}

The project specified in the '''Project''' box on the '''Details''' tab ('''Additional Details''' section) is used for the creation of sales orders, invoices, and service orders for the opportunity. This project is not used for the creation of project quotes based on the opportunity. Also, the project in this box does not reflect the connection with the project created based on the primary project quote of the opportunity.

The following activity will walk you through the process of creating a project quote and creating a project based on the project quote. You will also learn how project quotes are integrated with opportunities.[anchor|#_06df44a6-6513-4567-93b4-0a396ad7b340]((({S:Danger}The following activity is based on the ''U100'' dataset. If you are using another dataset, or if any system settings have been changed in ''U100'', these changes can affect the workflow of the activity and the results of the processing. To avoid any issues, restore the ''U100'' dataset to its initial state. ))){br}{TOC} ==Story== Suppose that the HM&rsquo;s Bakery and Cafe customer has ordered a juicer for one of its restaurants, along with the installation and training services. The sales manager has created an opportunity for the provision of the juicer and the services. Acting as an estimator, you will create a project quote for this opportunity, confirm the quote with the customer, and convert the quote to the project. ==Configuration Overview== For the purposes of this activity, the following features have been enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form:[anchor|#_4387db18-6b29-4015-8d96-56b9069f20d7] *''Project Accounting'', which provides support for the project accounting functionality *''Project Quotes'', which provides the ability to create project quotes *''Customer Management'', which provides the customer relation management (CRM) functionality, including management of opportunities
