with the settings from the following table (clearing the default settings in the specified columns); these settings establish cost by task and inventory item. #:{| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="16%" ! '''Inventory ID''' !width="16%" ! '''Quantity''' !width="16%" ! '''Ext. Price''' !width="16%" ! '''Project Task''' !width="16%" ! '''Cost Account Group''' !width="16%" ! '''Revenue Account Group''' |- | ''JUICER15'' | <tt>1.00</tt> | Cleared | ''PHASE1'' | ''MATERIAL'' | Cleared |- | ''INSTALL'' | <tt>4.00</tt> | Cleared | ''PHASE1'' | ''SUBCON'' | Cleared |- | ''TRAINING'' | <tt>8.00</tt> | Cleared | ''PHASE2'' | ''LABOR'' | Cleared |} #:Notice that the system automatically selects ''PHASE1'' as the project task in a new estimation line because this task is selected as the default for the project quote. #:You have cleared the '''Ext. Price''' and '''Revenue Account Group''' columns so that when this quote is converted to a project, the system will not convert these lines, which have no price and no revenue account group, to revenue budget lines of the project. #Add two more estimation lines with the settings from the following table; these settings establish revenue by task. #:{| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="37%" ! '''Description''' !width="18%" ! '''Ext. Price''' !width="18%" ! '''Project Task''' !width="25%" ! '''Revenue Account Group''' |- | <tt>The juicer with installation</tt> | <tt>2900.00</tt> | ''PHASE1'' | ''REVENUE'' |- | <tt>Training of employees</tt> | <tt>400.00</tt> | ''PHASE2'' | ''REVENUE'' |} #:Notice that for each of the added lines the '''Ext. Cost''' and '''Cost Account Group''' columns are empty. When this quote is converted to a project, the system will not convert these lines, which have no cost and cost account group, to cost budget lines of the project. #Save your changes to the project quote. #:In the Summary area, notice that the amount in the '''Total Sales''' box is ''3,300.00'', which is the total of the value