==Printing of a Project Quote ==
You can print a project quote with any status.{br}

On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_45_00|Project Quotes] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304500|PM304500]) form, you can print the selected project quote by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Print Quote''' on the form toolbar.{br}

If a project quote has been created based on an opportunity, you can also print a project quote on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR304000|CR304000]) form. To do this, on the '''Quotes''' tab, you select the project quote, and on the table toolbar, you click '''Print Quote'''.{br}

For the printing of project quotes, the system uses the [HelpRoot_ReportReference\PM_60_45_00|Project Quote] ([~/?ScreenId=PM604500|PM604500]) report. This report includes estimation lines, the header-level note, and the detailed description of a project quote.{br}

On the '''Billing Information''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_45_00|Project Quotes] form, you can specify the contact information of the customer to whom the project quote should be sent.

In Acumatica ERP, you can purchase materials and services on projects using purchase orders and accounts payable bills so that these purchases affect the cost budget of the projects.{br}{TOC}
==Learning Objectives==
You will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#ul_nwj_gch_tbb]
*Purchase materials and services for a project using a purchase order
*Receive materials purchased for a project to a warehouse
*Purchase services for a project using an accounts payable bill

==Applicable Scenarios==
You create a purchase order for a project if you want to purchase materials and services so that the purchase affect the cost budget of the project. You create an accounts payable bill for the same reasons if your purchase includes only services that do not require receiving to a warehouse.
==Configuring of Inventory for Processing Purchases on Projects==
To be able to purchase the following inventory items for projects, the corresponding accounts of the items must be mapped to an account group:[anchor|#_43fba96b-a55f-4a55-bae0-903fe80d497f]
*Stock items: The inventory account of the corresponding posting class specified in the '''Inventory/Accrual Account''' box on the '''GL Accounts''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_60_00|Posting Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN206000|IN206000]) form
*Non-stock items that do not require receipt—that is, the '''Require Receipt''' check box is cleared on the '''General Settings''' tab ('''Item Defaults''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form: The expense account of the item specified in the '''Expense Account''' box on the '''GL Accounts''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] form
*Non-stock items that require receipt—that is, the '''Require Receipt''' check box is selected on the '''General Settings''' tab ('''Item Defaults''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] form: The expense account of the corresponding posting class specified in the '''COGS/Expense Account''' box on the '''GL Accounts''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_60_00|Posting Classes] form

To be able to receive purchased stock items and non-stock items that require receipt to a warehouse, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_40_00|Warehouses] ([~/?ScreenId=IN204000|IN204000]) form, you need to create a separate location for each project task for which you are going to receive purchased inventory items to a warehouse.
==Processing of Purchase Orders for Projects==
You can purchase materials and services for projects using purchase orders of the ''Normal'' type. On the '''Document Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, to associate a purchase order line with a project, you specify the project and a project task.((({S:Hint}
If you do not want to associate a purchase order line with any project, you select the non-project code (''X'').{br}

You can process purchases for several projects with a single purchase order.
)))
If you select a sock item in a purchase order line, the line is assigned the ''Goods for IN'' type. When you select in a purchase order line a non-stock item that requires receipt—that is, the '''Require Receipt''' check box is selected for the non-stock item on the '''General Settings''' tab ('''Item Defaults''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form—the line is assigned the ''Non-Stock'' type. When you select in a purchase order line a non-stock item that does not require receipt, the line is assigned the ''Service'' type.((({S:Hint}If you purchase some material from a vendor directly to a customer and do not need to receive the material to your warehouse, you can create non-stock items that do not require receipt to represent these materials in the system. When you purchase such materials with a purchase order, you do not need to create a purchase receipt for them.
)))
You create a purchase receipt for the purchase order lines of the ''Goods for IN'' and ''Non-Stock'' types to receive the inventory items to the warehouse. On the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, you click '''Actions''' > '''Enter PO Receipt''' to create a purchase receipt. When you release the created purchase receipt on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form and the corresponding inventory receipt is released on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_10_00|Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=IN301000|IN301000]) form, the system updates the corresponding budget lines of the project with the same project task, account group (by the inventory or expense account), and inventory item on the '''Cost Budget''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form. The system updates the '''Actual Quantity''' and '''Actual Amount''' of these cost budget lines with the received quantity and amount.{br}

When you create an accounts payable bill for the purchase order lines of the ''Service'' type and release the bill on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form, the system updates the budget lines of the project with the same project task, account group (by the expense account), and inventory item on the '''Cost Budget''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form. The system updates the '''Actual Quantity''' and '''Actual Amount''' of these cost budget lines with the billed quantity and amount.{br}

For more information on processing purchase order, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\OrderMgmt_Standard_Inventory_Purchase_GeneralInfo|Standard Inventory Purchases: General Information].[anchor|#section_i3l_d4p_mcb]
