==Processing of Account Payable Bills for Projects==
You can purchase services for projects using accounts payable bills. A service is a non-stock item that does not require receipt—that is, the '''Require Receipt''' check box is cleared for the non-stock item on the '''General Settings''' tab ('''Item Defaults''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form.{br}

On the '''Document Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form, to associate a bill line with a non-stock item with a project, you specify the project and a project task.((({S:Hint}
If you do not want to associate a bill line with any project, you select the non-project code (''X'').{br}

You can purchase services for several projects with a single AP bill.
)))
When you release the account payable bill with lines related to a project, the system updates the budget lines of the project with the same project task, account group (by the expense account), and inventory item on the '''Cost Budget''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form. The system updates the '''Actual Quantity''' and '''Actual Amount''' of these cost budget lines with the billed quantity and amount.{br}

For more information on processing accounts payable bills, see [HelpRoot_Financials\Finance_ProcessingAPBills_GeneralInfo|AP Bills: General Info].
