When you process a purchase order for a project, you create purchase receipts and accounts payable bills. You can also create a standalone AP bill for a project. On release of the inventory receipt associated with the purchase receipt or the AP bill, the system generates the GL and project transactions described in the following sections.{br}{TOC}[anchor|#_c037f97e-7263-4315-8149-de10058ac719] ==GL Transactions Generated on Inventory Receipt Release== When an inventory receipt created on release of a purchase receipt prepared for a purchase order is released, the system creates a batch of the general ledger transactions shown in the following table.{br}
The system uses the following accounts as the source of the debited account in the GL batch it creates:[anchor|#_aa82c00d-a0b3-4af6-8da9-c7db9cc6c66b] *The inventory account, which is specified in the posting class of a stock item in the '''Inventory/Accrual Account''' box on the '''GL Accounts''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_60_00|Posting Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN206000|IN206000]) form. *The expense account, which is specified in the posting class of a non-stock item that requires receipt in the '''COGS/Expense Account''' box on the '''GL Accounts''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_60_00|Posting Classes] form. [anchor|#_df598bd6-3124-4958-a4d1-5ae4d706b031] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="30%" ! Account !width="23%" ! Source of Account !width="23%" ! Debit !width="23%" ! Credit |- | PO accrual account | Item | 0.00 | Amount |- | Inventory/expense account | Posting class of the item | Amount | 0.00 |} On the '''Financial Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_10_00|Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=IN301000|IN301000]) form, you can click the link in the '''Batch Nbr.''' box to view the details of the batch on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\GL_30_10_00|Journal Transactions] ([~/?ScreenId=GL301000|GL301000]) form.[anchor|#_8113a49c-c429-4b9b-8a62-7b68ba9dbb17] ==Project Transaction Generated on Inventory Receipt Release== When a batch of the general ledger transactions is created on release of the inventory receipt, the system also generates the project transaction shown in the table below.[anchor|#_15346d66-c39d-4998-a43d-912f939b6516] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="25%" ! Debit Account !width="25%" ! Credit Account !width="25%" ! Source of Account !width="25%" ! Amount |- | Inventory/expense account | | GL transaction | Amount |} You can review the created project transaction on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_40_10_00|Project Transaction Details] ([~/?ScreenId=PM401000|PM401000]) form. In the Selection area of this