Acumatica ERP supports the tracking of purchase orders for each project as project cost commitments, which gives you the ability to control purchases made for projects. When the commitments are created, the system uses them to populate the cost budget for the corresponding project, project task, inventory item, and account group.{br}{TOC} ==Learning Objectives== In this chapter, you will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#ul_e23_hhs_3cb] *Create commitments by processing a purchase order *Review the created commitments and the way they affect the project *Bill the purchase order and review how the commitments have been affected *Review the committed and actual values of the project budget
==Applicable Scenarios== If you want to distinguish purchases within the cost budget of a project, you use commitments, which you create by processing purchase orders with detail lines related to the project. The commitments update the cost budget of a project with purchased services and materials.[anchor|#section_akq_jg5_v1b] ==Tracking of Committed Costs for Projects== If the '''Internal Cost Commitment Tracking''' check box is selected on the '''General Settings''' tab ('''General Settings''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_10_10_00|Projects Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PM101000|PM101000]) form, the system exposes commitments on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_60_00|Commitments] ([~/?ScreenId=PM306000|PM306000]) form, as well as the following committed values of the project budget on the '''Cost Budget''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form:[anchor|#_38277968-084b-4271-bb38-4760c9294329] *'''Original Committed Quantity''' * '''Original Committed Amount''' * '''Revised Committed Quantity''' * '''Revised Committed Amount''' * '''Committed Open Quantity''' * '''Committed Open Amount''' * '''Committed Received Quantity''' * '''Committed Invoiced Quantity''' * '''Committed Invoiced Amount'''
The system creates a commitment for a purchase order line in the amount of the '''Ext. Cost''' of the line and updates the committed values of the corresponding budget line of a project on the '''Cost Budget''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] form if all of the following conditions are met on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form:[anchor|#_4e52f428-9748-49b9-8707-fca238501c14] *The type of the purchase order is ''Normal'' or ''Drop-Ship''. *The status of the purchase order is ''Pending Printing'', ''Pending Email'', or ''Open''. *The purchase order line specifies the project (and the applicable project task).
These commitments have the ''Internal'' type because they originate from documents created in the system, unlike commitments of the ''External'' type that can be imported into Acumatica ERP.{br}
On the '''Cost Budget''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] form, for each budget line, the system displays the total values of all the commitments that are associated with the same project, project task, account group, and inventory item.{br}
The initial commitment amount is displayed in the '''Original Committed Amount''' column and the '''Revised Committed Amount''' column. The '''Committed Open Amount''' of a new commitment is equal to the '''Revised Committed Amount'''.{br}
When you release an accounts payable bill with the purchase order lines of the ''Service'' type, the '''Committed Invoiced Quantity''' and '''Committed Invoiced Amount''' of the corresponding commitments are updated with the '''Quantity''' and '''Ext. Cost''' values of the bill lines, respectively. The '''Committed Invoiced Quantity''' and '''Committed Invoiced Amount''' are subtracted from the '''Committed Open Quantity''' and '''Committed Open Amount''' and added to the '''Actual Quantity''' and '''Actual Amount''', respectively.{br}
When an inventory receipt that corresponds to the purchase receipt with the purchase order lines of the ''Goods for IN'' or ''Non-Stock'' type is released, the '''Committed Received Quantity''' of the corresponding commitments is updated with the received quantity. The received quantity and the amount of the '''Ext. Cost''' of the related purchase order lines that correspond to the received quantity are subtracted from the '''Committed Open Quantity''' and '''Committed Open Amount''' and added to the '''Actual Quantity''' and '''Actual Amount''', respectively. When the purchase order lines of the ''Goods for IN'' or ''Non-Stock'' type are billed, the '''Committed Invoiced Quantity''' and '''Committed Invoiced Amount''' of the corresponding commitments are updated with the '''Quantity''' and '''Ext. Cost''' values of the bill lines, respectively.{br}
After a purchase order is received and billed fully, the '''Committed Open Quantity''' and '''Committed Open Amount''' of the corresponding commitment lines becomes zero. If a purchase order has been canceled, the incomplete amounts are subtracted from the '''Committed Open Amount'''. For more information about processing purchase orders for projects, see [HelpRoot_Projects\Projects_Project_Purchases_GeneralInfo|Processing Purchases on Projects: General Information].[anchor|#section_i3l_d4p_mcb] ==Workflow of Commitments== The following diagram illustrates the workflow of processing a commitment and the ways the commitment affects the project budget.[anchor|#fig_fhq_2nv_q2b][anchor|#image_ghq_2nv_q2b][image:UserGuide/Images/diag_Projects_Commitments_Workflow.png|popup|450px] ==Updating of Documents from Which Commitments Originate== You can update a purchase order from which a commitments originates. When you update the '''Ext. Cost''' of the purchase order line that refers to the project on the '''Document Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form and save the purchase order with the ''Pending Printing'', ''Pending Email'', or ''Open'' status, the system updates the '''Original Committed Amount''' and the '''Revised Committed Amount''' of the corresponding commitment. ==Recreating of Commitments== Although you usually do not need to recreate commitments, in rare cases, the committed values of the project budget may not match the underlying commitments. In such a case, you need to recreate commitments for a project. On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_50_40_00|Validate Project Balances] ([~/?ScreenId=PM504000|PM504000]) form, you select the '''Rebuild Commitments''' check box in the Summary area, select the check box in the unlabeled column in the table for the project, and click '''Validate''' on the form toolbar. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Projects\Projects_Project_Purchases_GeneralInfo|Processing Purchases on Projects: General Information]

