You can configure markups to charge the customer with each created change request. The following types of markup can be applied to a change request on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_85_00|Change Requests] ([~/?ScreenId=PM308500|PM308500]) form:[anchor|#_85dd3f3a-6d3d-45dd-9d8b-3af48d444b6b]
*Line-level markups: These markups apply to an individual estimation line on the '''Estimation''' tab.
*Document-level markups: These markups apply to the total line amount of the change request on the '''Markups''' tab.

You can override all markups and delete document-level markups at the change request level.
==Line-Level Markups==
A price markup is an item-specific markup. When you select an inventory item in an estimation line on the '''Estimation''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_85_00|Change Requests] ([~/?ScreenId=PM308500|PM308500]) form, the markup percent specified for the item is retrieved as the '''Price Markup (%)''' value. You can specify the price markup for the item on the '''Price/Cost Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_25_00|Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202500|IN202500]) form or on the '''Price/Cost Information''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form. If no price markup is specified for the item, the system uses the default price markup specified in the '''Default Price Markup, %''' box ('''Markup''' section) on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_10_10_00|Projects Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PM101000|PM101000]) form. If no default price markup is specified in the project accounting preferences, the price markup of the estimation line is zero.{br}

A line markup is defined at the account group level. When you select an account group in an estimation line in the '''Account Group''' column on the '''Estimation''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_85_00|Change Requests] form, the default markup specified for the account group is retrieved as the '''Line Markup (%)''' value. You can specify the default line markup for the account group on the '''Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_20_10_00|Account Groups] ([~/?ScreenId=PM201000|PM201000]) form. If no default markup is specified in the account group, the line markup of the estimation line is zero.{br}

The line amount of an estimation line considers the line-level markups and is calculated as follows:{br}

{{'''Unit Price''' = '''Unit Price''' + '''Unit Price''' * '''Price Markup (%)''' / <i>100<i>}}{br}

{{ '''Ext. Price''' = '''Quantity''' * '''Unit Price'''}}{br}

{{ '''Line Amount''' = '''Ext. Price''' + '''Ext. Price''' * '''Line Markup (%)''' / <i>100<i>}}
==Document-Level Markups==
A document-level markup applies to the total line amount of a change request. On the '''Markups''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_85_00|Change Requests] ([~/?ScreenId=PM308500|PM308500]) form, for a change request, you can define one or several document-level markups of the following types as well as define no markups:[anchor|#_fceb394e-b3c5-479a-bbeb-9fd1bc9f8c3f]
*''%'': A markup whose amount is calculated as follows:
*:{{Markup Amount = '''Line Total''' * <i>% Markup Value<i> / <i>100<i>}}
*:You can define as many markups of this type as necessary.
*''Cumulative %'': A markup whose amount is calculated as follows:
*:{{Markup Amount = (all the previously applied % markups) * <i>Cumulative % Value<i> / <i>100<i>}}
*:A markup of this type requires at least one markup of the ''%'' type.
*''Flat Fee'': A markup whose amount is specified manually to be added to the total markup.
*:You can define as many markups of this type as necessary.

A document-level markup is applied to a change request only if all the project budget key attributes—project task, account group, and optionally inventory item—are defined for the markup on the '''Markups''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_85_00|Change Requests] form.{br}

A change request inherits document-level markup from the project that you can define on the '''Settings''' tab ('''Document Markups''' table) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form. The project inherits document markups from the '''General Settings''' tab ('''Markup''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_10_10_00|Projects Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PM101000|PM101000]) form.

You prepare a budget forecast for a long-term project if you need to breakdown the structure of the project budget by financial periods. This gives you the ability to compare and analyze monthly budgets versus actual revenue and expenditures and control the budget performance by periods. ==Learning Objectives== In this chapter, you will learn how to:[anchor|#ul_nwj_gch_tbb] *Create a budget forecast for a project *Add financial periods to the budget forecast *Distribute budgeted values among the financial periods *Update the project budget based on the forecast *Update the forecast financial periods based on the updated actual values
==Applicable Scenarios== You create a budget forecast for a project if you need to breakdown the budget structure by financial periods to be able to control the budget performance by periods.[anchor|#section_fdf_x42_p2b] ==Creation of the Project Budget Forecast== Each project can have multiple revisions of the budget forecast. For a new project budget forecast, in the Summary area of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_20_96_00|Project Budget Forecast] ([~/?ScreenId=PM209600|PM209600]) form, you select the project and enter an alphanumeric revision identifier of the budget forecast, which must be unique within the project. When you enter the revision, the system automatically fills in the table with the revenue and cost budget lines of the selected project.{br}
In a forecast revision, you distribute original and revised budget amounts of existing revenue and cost budget lines among the financial periods in the selected range to estimate project revenue and expenses by periods.{br}
You can manually add financial periods for the selected budget line of the forecast revision by clicking '''Add Periods''' on the table toolbar and selecting the range of financial periods in the '''Add Periods''' dialog box.{br}
You can also make the system automatically add financial periods for all the project budget lines of the forecast revision listed in the table according to the selection criteria specified in the Summary area. When you click '''Generate Periods''' on the form toolbar, for each line in the table, the system adds periods based on the settings of the project task and related project transactions.{br}
Each financial period added for a project budget line of the forecast revision has quantities and amounts of zero. You can manually specify the '''Original Budgeted Quantity''', '''Original Budgeted Amount''', '''Revised Budgeted Quantity''', and '''Revised Budgeted Amount''' values for each period of the project budget line.{br}
You can also distribute the original and revised quantities and amounts of a project budget lines among period lines automatically by clicking '''Distribute''' on the form toolbar. In the '''Distribute''' dialog box, you define which values the system should distribute, in which columns, and for which budget lines. The distribution function rounds equally distributed values using the built-in logarithmic rounding algorithm. For an example of rounding, see [HelpRoot_Projects\Projects_Budget_Forecasts_Rounding|Creating Project Budget Forecasts: Example of Rounding].{br}
For each project budget line with added period lines, the system calculates the following totals in the '''Original Budgeted Quantity''', '''Original Budgeted Amount''', '''Revised Budgeted Quantity''', and '''Revised Budgeted Amount''' columns:[anchor|#_eb8115b3-a136-4595-93c5-02e6ce127d45] *'''Total''': The total of the period lines *'''Delta''': The difference between the value of the project budget line and the total of the period lines
==Processing Project Budget Forecasts== When actual values of a project are updated, the system automatically updates actual values of budget forecasts of the project, including period lines. The system calculates the differences between revised budgeted values and actual values in the '''Revised Quantity - Actual Quantity''' and '''Revised Amount - Actual Amount ''' columns on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_20_96_00|Project Budget Forecast] ([~/?ScreenId=PM209600|PM209600]) form so you can compare performance of each budget line by periods. If you need to update financial periods of a project budget line of the forecast revision, you click this line in the table on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_20_96_00|Project Budget Forecast] form, and on the table toolbar, click '''Update Forecast Lines'''. For the selected line, the system adds the financial periods to which actual values or change order values have been posted for the corresponding project budget line and that have been missed in the forecast revision.{br}
If you need to update the original and revised budgeted values of the corresponding project budget line on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] form with the delta values of a project budget line of the forecast revision, you click this line of the forecast revision in the table on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_20_96_00|Project Budget Forecast] form, and on the table toolbar, click '''Update Project Budget Line'''. ((({S:Warn}[anchor|#_fe402536-288f-40ac-a60a-28dac5fb96bc] *The system updates the original budgeted values of the projectonly if the project budget is not locked. For more information on locking the project budget, see [HelpRoot_Projects\Projects_Budget_Lock|Managing Project Budget: Locking of the Budget]. *The system updates the revised budgeted values of the project budget only if the change order workflow is disabled for the project. Otherwise, you must use change orders to update the project budget. For more information on change orders, see [HelpRoot_Projects\Projects_CO_GeneralInfo|Managing Changes in Projects: General Information]. )))

The following activity will walk you through the process of creating and processing a project budget forecast.[anchor|#_6d16d525-0a49-4577-870b-40d1e22d5119]((({S:Danger}The following activity is based on the ''U100'' dataset. If you are using another dataset, or if any system settings have been changed in ''U100'', these changes can affect the workflow of the activity and the results of the processing. To avoid any issues, restore the ''U100'' dataset to its initial state. ))) ==Story== Suppose that the HM&rsquo;s Bakery and Cafe customer has ordered 80 hours of new-employee training on operating juicers. The project accountant has created a project to account for the provided training.{br}
The project accountant wants to prepare a budget forecast by periods to be able to compare and analyze monthly budgets versus actual costs within the project work breakdown structure. Because the training will take place in January and February, the project accountant wants to distribute the total budget across the periods when this work is going to be performed for further review and analysis of budget performance.{br}
Acting as the project accountant, you will create a project budget forecast. Distributing the budget across periods, you will realize that the budget will require an update. You will update the project budget based on the budget forecast. When the training takes place, you will update the progress of the project and review the budget forecast. ==Configuration Overview== For the purposes of this activity, the following features have been enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form:[anchor|#_4387db18-6b29-4015-8d96-56b9069f20d7] *''Project Accounting'', which provides support for the project accounting functionality *''Budget Forecasts'', which gives you the ability to create budget forecasts for projects
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form, the ''HMBAKERY13'' project has been created and the ''TRAINING'' project task has been created for the project. Also, the revenue budget and the cost budget is defined with the line with the ''TRAINING'' inventory item and the ''LABOR'' account group for the project.{br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_40_00|Project Transactions] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304000|PM304000]) form, the ''PM00000020'' batch of project transactions related to the project has been created. ==Process Overview== In this activity, you will create the first revision of the budget forecast and generate periods for the revision on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_20_96_00|Project Budget Forecast] ([~/?ScreenId=PM209600|PM209600]) form. On this form, you will then distribute budgeted amounts by periods and update the project budget based on the distributed values. You will update actual values of the project by releasing transactions on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_40_00|Project Transactions] ([~/?ScreenId=PM304000|PM304000]) form. You will finally update the budget forecast on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_20_96_00|Project Budget Forecast] form based on the updated actual values. ==System Preparation== To sign in to the system and prepare to perform the instructions of the activity, do the following:[anchor|#_6c9e4914-0e56-4fc0-9f9d-df880dcd99b6] #Launch the Acumatica ERP website, and sign in to a company with the U100 dataset preloaded as Pam Brawner by using the ''brawner'' username and the ''123'' password.
