This topic explains how to allocate multiple projects, and how the system generates, changes, or works with projects as a result of the mass processing.{br}{TOC}[anchor|#_d1c62523-0979-4c7b-ab91-7bd059f4f115] ==Mass-Allocating Projects== You can initiate allocating for multiple projects on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_50_25_00|Run Allocations by Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM502500|PM502500]) form; this allocating entails the creation of allocation transactions. On this form, you select the unlabeled check boxes in the rows of the projects to be processed in the table, and you click '''Allocate''' on the form toolbar. The system initiates allocating for the selected projects. Allocation transactions will be created for only those projects that have the tasks with an associated allocation rule.{br}
To initiate processing for all the projects listed in the table of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_50_25_00|Run Allocations by Projects] form, you click '''Allocate All''' on the form toolbar. The system initiates allocating for all the projects listed in the table.[anchor|#_e7d1a0d9-01a7-48cd-90e7-75fed7de23a6] ==Mass-Allocating Project Tasks== You can initiate allocating for multiple project tasks on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_50_20_00|Run Allocations by Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=PM502000|PM502000]) form; this allocating entails the creation of allocation transactions. On this form, which displays only those project tasks that have an associated allocation rule, you select the unlabeled check boxes in the rows of the project tasks to be processed in the table, and you click '''Allocate''' on the form toolbar. The system initiates allocating for the selected project tasks.{br}
To initiate processing for all the project tasks listed in the table of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_50_20_00|Run Allocations by Tasks] form, you click '''Allocate All''' on the form toolbar. The system initiates allocating for all the project tasks listed in the table. ==Mass-Releasing Reversing Allocation Transaction== To mass-release project transactions, including reversing allocation transaction, you use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_50_10_00|Release Transactions] ([~/?ScreenId=PM501000|PM501000]) form. On this form, you select the unlabeled check boxes in the rows of the transactions to be released and click '''Release''' on the form toolbar to process the selected transactions; alternatively, you can click '''Release All''' to process all the transactions shown in the table.

Acumatica ERP supports the use of corporate credit cards on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_10_00|Expense Claim] ([~/?ScreenId=EP301000|EP301000]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_10_20|Expense Receipt] ([~/?ScreenId=EP301020|EP301020]) forms. This helps employees to categorize and track the expenses, including the expenses related to a project. For example, while in the field, your employees can buy something that they want to charge on a project and pay for it with a corporate card. Employees can still have out-of-pocket expenses that are reimbursed through the standard process.{br}{TOC} ==Learning Objectives== In this chapter, you will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#_d0dffcc8-792b-41cf-a4d7-1a17e54017d3] *Create a GL account, cash account, and payment method for a corporate credit card *Create a corporate credit card in the system *Create an expense receipt for company&rsquo;s expenses paid the corporate credit card *Process an expense claim for the expense receipt paid with the corporate credit card *Process personal expenses paid with the corporate credit card *Process company&rsquo;s expenses paid with a personal account *Reconcile a bank statement for the corporate credit card *Create and release a bill for the bank
==Applicable Scenarios== You process an expense receipt with a corporate credit card when you want to record expenses paid by a company corporate credit card. ==Configuration of Corporate Cards== You configure corporate credit cards on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CA_20_25_00|Corporate Cards] ([~/?ScreenId=CA202500|CA202500]) form. You enter the card number for matching transactions on a bank statement. Multiple employees can use a single corporate card; you add these employees to the table on the form.{br}
In order to create corporate cards on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CA_20_25_00|Corporate Cards] form, GL accounts, cash accounts, payment methods, and employees must be configured as described below.{br}
You configure a separate GL account for each bank and currency. For each GL account, you create a separate cash account with the following settings on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CA_20_20_00|Cash Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CA202000|CA202000]) form:[anchor|#_0318118d-544d-4ea4-a2b6-080040eb38b7] *The '''Clearing Account''' check box is cleared. *The '''Restrict Visibility with Branch''' check box is cleared. *The '''Use for Corporate Cards''' check box is selected. *Only one payment method can be associated with the cash account. *Optionally, the '''Requires Reconciliation''' check box is selected; if it is, a numbering sequence must be specified in the '''Reconciliation Numbering Sequence''' box. The predefined ''CARECON'' numbering sequence can be selected. {br}
Although the cash account that is used for a corporate card must have only one associated payment method, this payment method can be selected for multiple cash accounts. If a payment method is selected for a cash account that is used for a corporate card, in the Summary area of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CA_20_40_00|Payment Methods] ([~/?ScreenId=CA204000|CA204000]) form, the '''Use in AP''' check box is selected. Also, on the '''Settings for Use in AP''' tab of the form, this payment method should have the following settings:[anchor|#_88735079-9395-4939-973b-95bc4b462db3] *'''Not Required''' ('''Additional Processing''' section): Selected *'''Require Unique Payment Ref.''' ('''Payment Settings''' section): Cleared
If the card currency differs from the currency of an employee who uses the corporate card, for this employee, the '''Enable Currency Override''' and '''Enable Rate Override''' check boxes must be selected on the '''General Info''' tab ('''Employee Settings''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_30_00|Employees] ([~/?ScreenId=EP203000|EP203000]) form. (The '''Currency ID''' box, where the employee currency is specified, can also be found in this section of the form.) ==Payment of Expense Receipts with Corporate Cards== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_10_20|Expense Receipt] ([~/?ScreenId=EP301020|EP301020]) form, you create expense receipts to the employee that is associated with you user. You can also create expense receipts for any subordinates of that employee. In the '''Paid With''' box (in the '''Expense Details '''section of the '''Receipt Details''' tab), you select how the expense receipt has been paid. The following options are available:[anchor|#_1411788c-144d-4520-a3e0-8f3e519271a5] *''Personal Account'': The company&rsquo;s expenses that the employee paid with his or her own funds and the company will need to reimburse this amount to you. This is the default option if the employee has no active corporate card assigned. *''Corporate Card, Company Expense'': The company&rsquo;s expenses that are paid with a corporate card. This is the default option if the employee has an active corporate card assigned. *''Corporate Card, Personal Expense'': The employee&rsquo;s personal expenses that are paid with a corporate card.
In the '''Corporate Card''' box, you select a corporate card associated with the employee. The default corporate card, if any, is selected as follows:[anchor|#_fa68e37c-f829-43e1-a6d0-98e9b677a9d5] *The corporate card used in the employee&rsquo;s most recent expense receipt is selected, if it is available. The most recent receipt is determined by the receipt&rsquo;s creation date. *If the corporate card that was used most recently is unavailable—that is, inactive, deleted, or no longer assigned to the employee—the employee&rsquo;s only active card or the first active card the system finds for the employee. The first corporate card is the first card in the employee&rsquo;s card list; this list is sorted alphabetically by name.
Corporate card expenses cannot be split. That is, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_10_20|Expense Receipt] form, in the '''Expense Details''' section of the '''Receipt Details''' tab, the '''Employee Part''' of an expense receipt paid with a corporate card must be zero.{br}
The '''Ref. Nbr.''' box, you enter the reference number that usually matches the number of the original receipt. ==Claiming of Expense Receipts Paid with Corporate Cards== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_10_00|Expense Claim] ([~/?ScreenId=EP301000|EP301000]) form, you can claim with a single expense claim all the employee's expense receipts paid with corporate cards as long as they have the same card currency. Each expense claim line on the '''Expense Claim Details''' tab refers to an expense receipt. If you create a new expense claim line on the form that does not originate from any expense receipt, on release of the expense claim, the system creates the corresponding expense receipt for that expense claim line.{br}
On release of an expense claim, the system creates documents as follows for the expense claim lines, depending on the value in the '''Paid With''' column:[anchor|#_0497cdd1-5185-401c-ad2a-29b56b794f48] *''Personal Account'': A single AP bill is created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form for all the expense claim lines with positive amounts and a single AP debit adjustment is created on the same form for all the expense claim lines with negative amounts. *''Corporate Card, Company Expense'': An AP quick check is created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_40_00|Quick Checks] ([~/?ScreenId=AP304000|AP304000]) form for each expense claim line, if the '''Post Summarized Corporate Card Company Expenses''' check box is cleared on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_10_10_00|Time and Expenses Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=EP101000|EP101000]) form. *:If the '''Post Summarized Corporate Card Company Expenses''' check box in selected, the system creates a separate AP quick check for each group of the expense claim lines with the same date, corporate card, and reference number. *''Corporate Card, Personal Expense'': A single AP debit adjustment is created on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] form for all the expense claim lines. [anchor|#section_i3l_d4p_mcb] ==Workflow of Claiming Expenses Paid with Corporate Cards== The following diagram illustrates the workflow of claiming an expense paid with a corporate credit card.[anchor|#fig_fhq_2nv_q2b][anchor|#image_ghq_2nv_q2b][image:UserGuide/Images/diag_Expense_Receipt_Workflow.png|popup|350px]

